The paper deals with event-based cameras and proposes a neural asynchronous approach to process event streams. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper leverages deep neural networks, indicating that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also presents experimental results, suggesting that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper deals with motion estimation, which could suggest that it belongs to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach, indicating that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
